body:
@jdfreder I don't have strong feelings regarding stickyness, but here are two good things about it:
- a priori it doesn't slow down common actions (like select all (running) notebooks and shutdown), and can significantly speed up rarer ones (like select idle notebooks).
- more importantly, when clicking on an "undetermined" checkbox, the user usually doesn't know the outcome of clicking (whether it's going to select all or none), and actually expects to be able to click twice in case he doesn't get the result he wants.
